      • FORM_ERR_WARN_DISPLAY

        public static final java.lang.String FORM_ERR_WARN_DISPLAY
        Name to be given to the control on which, validation errors and warnings and other messages will be displayed. When an error/warning occurs on performing a field validation, the error/warning message will be displayed on this named control. Sample code: 
         Label messageDisplayLabel = new Label(composite, style);
 messageDisplayLabel.setData(YRCConstants.YRC_CONTROL_NAME, YRCConstants.FORM_ERR_WARN_DISPLAY);

        See Also:

      • FILE_UPLOAD_ONSELECT

        public static final java.lang.String FILE_UPLOAD_ONSELECT
        ONSELECT and ONSUBMIT are the supported file upload types. They are permissible values for the property 'sc.file.upload.type' to be specified in yfs.properties and can be overridden for a file upload control through the binding data. File upload type "ONSELECT" indicates the file has to be queued for a file upload, as soon as the file is registered.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FILE_UPLOAD_ONSUBMIT

        public static final java.lang.String FILE_UPLOAD_ONSUBMIT
        ONSELECT and ONSUBMIT are the supported file upload types. They are permissible values for the property 'sc.file.upload.type' to be specified in yfs.properties and can be overridden for a file upload control through the binding data File upload type "ONSUBMIT" indicates the file has to be uploaded when it is required by a API.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FILE_UPLOAD_MAX_FILE_SIZE

        public static final java.lang.String FILE_UPLOAD_MAX_FILE_SIZE
        It is used for file upload functionality. The property indicates maximum file upload size.The property has to be specified in yfs.properties globally and can be specified at the application level as well
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FILE_UPLOAD_ALLOWED_TYPES

        public static final java.lang.String FILE_UPLOAD_ALLOWED_TYPES
        It is used for file upload functionality. The property indicates allowed file types.The property has to be specified in yfs.properties globally and can be specified at the application level as well
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ERROR_FILE

        public static final int ERROR_FILE
        Error type to indicate file validation error. It will be used in connection with file upload functionality
        See Also:

      • FILE_UPLOAD_TYPE

        public static final java.lang.String FILE_UPLOAD_TYPE
